&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/sort-array-by-parity/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2023-09-28&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;È°åÁõÆÊïòËø∞&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given an integer array  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt; , move all the even integers at the beginning of the array followed by all the odd integers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;any array&lt;/strong&gt; that satisfies this condition&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: nums = [3,1,2,4]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: [2,4,3,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: The outputs [4,2,3,1], [2,4,1,3], and [4,2,1,3] would also be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: nums = [0]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: [0]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
