 &lt;p&gt;‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicate-letters/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2023-09-26&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;È°åÁõÆÊïòËø∞&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given a string  &lt;code&gt;s&lt;/code&gt; , remove duplicate letters so that every letter appears once and only once. You must make sure your result is &lt;strong&gt;the smallest in lexicographical order&lt;/strong&gt; among all possible results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;note info no-icon&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lexicographically Smaller&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A string a is lexicographically smaller than a string b if in the first position where a and b differ, string a has a letter that appears earlier in the alphabet than the corresponding letter in b.&lt;br /&gt;
If the first min(a.length, b.length) characters do not differ, then the shorter string is the lexicographically smaller one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: s = &amp;quot;bcabc&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;abc&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: s = &amp;quot;cbacdcbc&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;acdb&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
